1. Use prepared statements: 
In some methods, you are using parameterized queries, which is a good practice. However, you can further optimize it by using prepared statements. A prepared statement is a feature of SQLite that allows you to pre-compile and optimize a query before executing it. This can improve performance, especially when you are executing the same query multiple times with different parameters. Here is an example of how to use prepared statements:

```
var command = new SQLiteCommand(connection);
