The `init_data()` function initializes the cache and data items. `is_in_cache()` checks if a data item is already in the cache. `update_cache()` updates the cache with a new data item. `find_data()` checks if a data item can be found in the hot or cold data items based on the given probability. `generate_query()` generates a query with an exponentially distributed wait time and checks if the data item is in the cache or can be found in the server. `generate_update()` generates a new data item update and stores it in the hot or cold data items based on the given probability. `server()` generates a data item update with an exponentially distributed wait time. `client()` repeatedly generates queries.

