In `sqlite-net-pcl`, you can define a ForeignKey relationship in the model classes and use it when querying data. To use foreign keys in `UserCard` class:

1. Create a `User` property in the `UserCard` class, then define the foreign key relationship by adding `[ForeignKey(typeof(User))]` attribute to `UserId`.

2. Create a `Card` property in the `UserCard` class and define the foreign key relationship by adding `[ForeignKey(typeof(Card))]` attribute to `CardId`.

Here's the updated `UserCard` class:

```csharp
public class UserCard
{
    [PrimaryKey, AutoIncrement]
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [ForeignKey(typeof(User))]
    public string UserId { get; set; }

    [ForeignKey(typeof(Card))]
    public string CardId { get; set; }

    public long Timestamp { get; set; }

    [ManyToOne(CascadeOperations = CascadeOperation.CascadeInsert)] // Fetches User when loading UserCard
    public User User { get; set; }

    [ManyToOne(CascadeOperations = CascadeOperation.CascadeInsert)] // Fetches Card when loading UserCard
    public Card Card { get; set; }

    public UserCard() { }

    public UserCard(User user, Card card, long timestamp)
    {
        User = user;
        UserId = user.Id;
        Card = card;
        CardId = card.Id;
        Timestamp = timestamp;
    }
}
```

