{
    var userCardsQuery = @"
        SELECT UserCard.*, User.*, Card.*
        FROM UserCard
        JOIN User ON User.Id = UserCard.UserId
        JOIN Card ON Card.Id = UserCard.CardId;
    ";

    // Parse the result and fill UserCard.User and UserCard.Card manually
    var userCards = new List<UserCard>();
    await _connection.ExecuteScalarAsync(userCardsQuery, (userCard, user, card) =>
    {
        userCard.User = user;
        userCard.Card = card;

        userCards.Add(userCard);
    });

    return userCards;
}
```

In this example, we use the `ExecuteScalarAsync` method for executing the query and use the callback to parse the result and fill in the `User` and `Card` properties of the `UserCard` instances manually.

Keep in mind that `sqlite-net-pcl` does not have built-in support for writing join queries, so you need to write the join queries manually as shown above.

